description:
Prisoners are demeaned through every possible avenue,
even down to the clothes they're allowed to wear.
name: Prisoner's Loincloth

description:
Wretched cursed armor that bears the visage of its 
victims. The humanity of those trapped within is lost.
name: The Warden

description:
Brown and soiled.
It barely fits you, no matter how large you may be.
name: Baggy Breeches

description:
A bronze phylactery shaped into a towering shield.
The wearer sacrifices her very life energy for power.
name: Fridenot's Tower Shield

description:
Salts that bolden the body and the mind. The miners for
these odious salts often go mad from days without sleep. Addicting.
name: Huffing Salts

description:
An innocuous bronze ring. When worn, the power of
magical keys is unlocked.
name: Ancient Key Ring

description:
Unlocks the lost power of Sequester.
Rusted, and the blade is missing.
name: Convict's Key

description:
Unlocks the lost power of Banishment.
Angular.
name: Torturer's Key

description:
A healing powder. Although taboo for its euphoric effects,
thousands of acres are dedicated to its cultivation.
name: Giggledust

description: Adds Soul Tap.
name: Stained Shackle

description:
A ceremonial blindfold of sacred purple cloth. Cursed.
What is invisible may only become revealed when blind.
name: Blindfold

description:
A substance that, when smoked, heightens the focus
and soothes the nerves, but induces lethargy.
name: Pouch-o'-Snuff

description: Adds Expurge.
name: Abyssal Grimoire

description:
Adds Dark Ritual. The tarnished remains of a court
mage who studied the art of efficient spellcasting.
name: Pendulum's Eyechain

description:
Purple used to denote aristocracy and the wealth of a
nation.
name: Purple Robes

description: Exceptionally modest.
name: Loincloth

description: The second stage of the malignant Curse.
name: Flagellant's Dark Hand

description:
A sphere of immense demonic power. 
Unlocks the Inert Curse.
name: Idol of Malefice

description: Adds Taunt.
name: Challenger's Ear Necklace

description:
A ceremonial dagger with a hilt of deep purple. Its
shape allows the easy removal of eyes from the socket.
name: Ritual Dagger

description:
A halberd light enough for the offhand. Useful for
gaining distance.
name: Pikenshot Halberd

description: Adds Hunter's Hex.
name: Heretic's Charm

description:
A confiscated text whose allure surpassed the call of
duty.
name: Heretical Text

description:
A headgear which obscures the face. Behind the cloth is
a metal casing for the wearer's head.
name: Capirote

description:
A sickening blackened hand, sawed off by the wrist.
Adds Calcified Curse.
name: Curseplague Ridden Hand

description:
A doll made out of dried boar skin. 
A fetish for certain hexes.
name: Tearing Doll
